  "content": "<p>1\ufe0f\u20e32\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 12th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>I believe a fundamental aspect of OS security must be a secure way to return the OS into a well-defined, secure state if a compromise has been identified.</p><p>Fending of an attacker is one thing, accepting that it might happen anyway and that you can recover from that in a reasonable way is another. And that&#39;s the case not only if you think about &quot;cattle&quot; style installs\u2026</p>",
